30		Message number
13 message ~	names
Message_13 from Grock:  semicolons
~
A message from Grock lies here.
~
If you want to use a semicolon as a semicolon, and not as a newline, you
must escape it with a backslash.  In otherwords, type backslash-semicolon.
kinda like this:
\;
If this doesn't work, try escaping it with another semicolon.  example:
;;

If you have any problems with this let me know.
Grock

~
